<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF796AC6FD199D9C1D48B6A8" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF796AC6FD199D9C1D48B6A8" blockId="130.[739,1333,2934,3361]" lastBlockId="130.[126,1331,3369,3482]" pageId="130" pageNumber="889">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FD199D9C1DD1B0D4" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[741,977,3013,3046]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">Scotophilus nigrita</taxonomicName>
was mostly referred to as S. gigas until in 1978 when it was concluded that it is the senior name for the taxon; prior to 1978, specimens called 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FB239A621B33B76E" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1247,1331,3131,3164]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita</taxonomicName>
should be 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FC879A3A1DE9B7B6" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[891,1001,3171,3204]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dinganii">dinganii</taxonomicName>
. Based on cytochromeb analyses, S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FC4A9AD31A0BB799" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[950,1035,3210,3243]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita</taxonomicName>
is paraphyletic with respect to S. colias, S. dinganui, S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FB299AEB1D0BB7C8" authorityName="de Winton" authorityYear="1899" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigritellus">nigritellus</taxonomicName>
, and S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FC7C9A801DD0B7C8" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1852" box="[896,976,3289,3322]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">viridis</taxonomicName>
. Populations of S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FB239A801B34B7C8" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[1247,1332,3289,3322]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita</taxonomicName>
from West and southern Africa differ genetically by 7-6-8-1%), suggesting that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF796AC6FD549B701CFDB678" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[680,765,3369,3402]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="889" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nigrita">nigrita</taxonomicName>
might be distinct from alvenslebeni, but more extensive genetic sampling and morphological analyses are needed to take any taxonomic conclusion. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
